PLAGUE, FATAL - CHINA: (GANSU)
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 10 Dec 2007
Source: XinHuaNet [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2007-12/10/content_7226599.htm>


China's northwest Gansu Province reported its 2nd plague case in 2007
in November, China's Ministry of Health said here on Monday [10 Dec
2007]. The patient died, the ministry said in its monthly report on
infectious diseases. No further details were provided.

Gansu also reported China's 1st plague case of 2007 in September.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett

[No information is given regarding either case. Deaths in _Y. pestis_
infection usually relate to bacteremia and/or pneumonia. A map of
China showing the north-central Gansu province can be found at:
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gansu>.
- Mod.LL]

[Plague cases in north China near the Mongolian border are usually in
marmot hunters who get it from bites from their infected fleas or from
contact with infected blood while skinning the marmots. - Mod.JW]
